name: ase-notebook
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "ase-notebook" %}
{% set version = "0.3.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 79e9ca9ca50b0c00e5bdb90b4cb02eebe9fbac8cd48da1ddec7f0d1330a75791

build:
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - ase-notebook.view_atoms = ase_notebook.viewer:launch_gui_exec
  noarch: python
  script: '{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv '

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.5
    - setuptools
  run:
    - ase >=3.18,<4
    - attrs >=19,<20
    - importlib_resources >=1,<2
    - ipywidgets >=7.5,<8
    - matplotlib-base >=3.1,<4
    - numpy >=1.16
    - python >=3.5
    - pythreejs >=2.1,<3
    - svgutils >=0.3,<0.4
    - svgwrite >=1.3,<2

test:
  imports:
    - ase_notebook
    - ase_notebook.backend
    - ase_notebook.data

about:
  home: https://github.com/chrisjsewell/ase-notebook
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Highly configurable 2D (SVG) & 3D (threejs) visualisations for ASE/Pymatgen structures, within the Jupyter Notebook
  doc_url: https://ase-notebook.readthedocs.io/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - chrisjsewell
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
